courses.learning_outcomes:
Upon completion of the course, students will be expected to:

1. Be able to describe the scopes and principles of occupational health and hygiene;

2. Understand common occupational hazards, occupational diseases and relevant legislations;

3. Know basic skills of health risk assessment and conducting occupational health hazards evaluation;

4. Be conversant with the basic techniques in assessing occupational exposures, controlling occupational hazards, and occupational epidemiology in practice;

5. Be articulate in linkage of occupational and environmental health and workplace sustainability;

By the end of this course, students should be able to:

1. Capture an overview of major theories in the sociological study of health and medicine;

2. Explain how social factors influence health and wellbeing and shape health inequalities;

3. Describe social meanings of illness and the social consequences of defining behaviors and conditions as illnesses;

4. Aware of social functions of health organizations and institutions;

5. Critically evaluate empirical studies in the field of medical sociology;

6. Analyze health-related issues in Chinese societies from sociological perspectives.
